  "prompt": "How does international law intersect with national laws on money laundering?",
  "response": "International law and national laws on money laundering intersect in several important ways:\n\n1. International Conventions and Treaties\n- UN Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- These provide standardized frameworks for combating money laundering\n\n2. Mutual Legal Assistance\n- Countries collaborate to investigate and prosecute cross-border money laundering\n- Sharing of financial intelligence and evidence\n- Extradition arrangements for financial criminals\n\n3. Regulatory Harmonization\n- Countries adopt similar legal standards for:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Financial institution compliance requirements\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- International organizations like INTERPOL assist in investigations\n- Coordinated efforts to track and freeze illicit financial assets\n- Sanctions against countries with weak anti-money laundering frameworks\n\n5. Compliance Requirements\n- Banks and financial institutions must implement international standards\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) protocols\n- Reporting suspicious transactions\n- Risk-based compliance approaches\n\n6. Technological Challenges\n- Emergence of cryptocurrencies\n- Cross-border digital financial transactions\n- Need for adaptive international legal frameworks\n\nThese intersections create complex multilateral approaches to preventing financial crimes.",
